    "body": "The [USEARCH download request form](https://www.drive5.com/usearch/download.html) generates a unique download for every request of the software, embedding the requestors email address into the binary.  For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\n./usearch10.0.240_i86linux32\r\nusearch v10.0.240_i86linux32, 4.0Gb RAM (32.9Gb total), 8 cores\r\n(C) Copyright 2013-17 Robert C. Edgar, all rights reserved.\r\nhttp://drive5.com/usearch\r\n\r\nLicense: user@example.com\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf initiating the download from a \"trusted source,\" do I just use `--no-checksum` to bypass the check if installing it as an explicit package?\r\n\r\nIf not explicitly installed, how can I bypass the checksum of a dependency without ignoring checksums for the entire package?\r\n\r\n",
